# NOTICE

This project includes work derived from the original
"gbmonctl" project by Kelvie Wong (<https://github.com/kelvie/gbmonctl>),
licensed under the MIT License.

Substantial modifications, extensions, and re-architecture
have been made since the fork, including:

- Expanded property tables (standard VCP, vendor extensions)
- Support for read, write, and momentary VCP types
- Cross-platform build system (Makefile, VS Code tasks, MSYS2 toolchains)
- Extended usage flags
  - Multi-monitor support
  - Enhanced parsing and error handling

The original portions remain copyright (c) 2025 Kelvie Wong
and are licensed under the MIT License. All other portions are
copyright (c) 2025 Leo van Alphen and licensed under the Apache License 2.0.

The MIT License below applies solely to portions of code originating from the gbmonctl project.

